{"id":"math120-critical_pt120-002","cid":"MATH 120","topic":"Applications of Derivatives","subtopic":"Optimization","difficulty":2,"license":"CC BY-NC-SA (Numberbender original)","instruction":"Revenue is R(x) = {a}x^2 + {b}x + {c}. Find the number of units x that maximizes revenue, and compute that maximum revenue.","params":{"a":{"type":"int","min":-3,"max":-1},"b":{"type":"int","min":12,"max":36},"c":{"type":"int","min":0,"max":80}},"answer_expr":"critical_pt120","steps":["Differentiate: R'(x) = {two_a}x + {b}.","Set equal to zero and solve: x = {x_star}.","Maximum revenue = R({x_star}) = {fx_star}."],"tags":["survey-calculus","optimization","revenue","maximum"]}
